{
  "page": "Wyvern",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Wyvern_by_Kevin_Catalan.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f5/Wyvern_by_Kevin_Catalan.jpg/400px-Wyvern_by_Kevin_Catalan.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"275\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f5/Wyvern_by_Kevin_Catalan.jpg/600px-Wyvern_by_Kevin_Catalan.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f5/Wyvern_by_Kevin_Catalan.jpg/800px-Wyvern_by_Kevin_Catalan.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Wyvern_by_Kevin_Catalan.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A wyvern, by Kevin Catalan ©</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Wyverns</b> are a species of reptile that dwells in <a href=\"/index.php/Sothoryos\" title=\"Sothoryos\">Sothoryos</a>, kin to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a>, although they do not breathe <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonflame\" title=\"Dragonflame\">fire</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf834_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf834-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Characteristics\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Characteristics</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Characteristics\">Characteristics</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wyvern&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Characteristics\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Wyverns have great leathery wings, \"cruel\" beaks, and an insatiable hunger. They are more ferocious than <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a>, if smaller in size. Wyverns are called \"the tyrants of the southern skies\", and are one of the reasons why <a href=\"/index.php/Sothoryos\" title=\"Sothoryos\">Sothoryos</a> is thinly populated.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf834_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf834-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Varieties of wyverns include brindled wyverns, swamp wyverns, brownbellies, and shadow-wings. Brindled wyverns have green-and-white scales, and grow up to thirty feet long. Swamp wyverns may grow larger than that, but they are mostly inactive and rarely fly far from their lairs. Brownbellies, though not much bigger than <a href=\"/index.php/Monkey\" title=\"Monkey\">monkeys</a>, hunt in packs of a hundred or more, and so are far more dangerous than larger breeds. The shadow-wing wyvern is nocturnal, with black scales and wings that make it invisible in the dark, and therefore is the most feared.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf834_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf834-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wyvern&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Vyrwel_2.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/85/House_Vyrwel_2.svg/200px-House_Vyrwel_2.svg.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"220\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/85/House_Vyrwel_2.svg/300px-House_Vyrwel_2.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/85/House_Vyrwel_2.svg/400px-House_Vyrwel_2.svg.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Vyrwel_2.svg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The arms of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Vyrwel\" title=\"House Vyrwel\">House Vyrwel</a></div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Wyvern_Point\" title=\"Wyvern Point\">Wyvern Point</a> in northern <a href=\"/index.php/Sothoryos\" title=\"Sothoryos\">Sothoryos</a> is named after the creature, which hunts above its swamps and jungles.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafwyvern_point.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafwyvern_point.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>, the sigil of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Vyrwel\" title=\"House Vyrwel\">House Vyrwel</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Darkdell\" title=\"Darkdell\">Darkdell</a> depicts a wyvern.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The castle of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> includes wyverns among its stone <a href=\"/index.php/Gargoyle\" title=\"Gargoyle\">gargoyles</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wyvern&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Barth\" title=\"Barth\">Barth</a> wrote about wyverns in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Dragons,_Wyrms,_and_Wyverns:_Their_Unnatural_History\" title=\"Dragons, Wyrms, and Wyverns: Their Unnatural History\">Dragons, Wyrms, and Wyverns: Their Unnatural History</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and he speculated that <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodmages\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bloodmages\">bloodmages</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a> may have created <a href=\"/index.php/Dragons\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragons\">dragons</a> using wyvern stock.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf834_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf834-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/56_AC\" title=\"56 AC\">56&#160;AC</a> a report came to the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> from one of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Rego_Draz\" title=\"Rego Draz\">Rego Draz</a>'s agents, which claimed that a dragon was being displayed in the fighting pits of <a href=\"/index.php/Astapor\" title=\"Astapor\">Astapor</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a>. It was at the same time when King Jaehaerys was looking for <a href=\"/index.php/Balerion\" title=\"Balerion\">Balerion</a>, on whom <a href=\"/index.php/Aerea_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerea Targaryen\">Aerea Targaryen</a> had escaped <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> two years earlier. Barth dismissed these claims, however, declaring that it was without a doubt a wyvern mistaken for a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> by people who had never seen a dragon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_scenes\">Behind the scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wyvern&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In British heraldry, a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wyvern\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Wyvern\">wyvern</a> is defined as a winged dragon with two legs and a barbed tail.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> In <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i>, all dragons have two legs, and wyverns are considered \"kin\" but not a subspecies of dragon.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wyvern&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Not_a_Blog\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Not a Blog\">Not a Blog</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://grrm.livejournal.com/327410.html?thread=17927666#t17927666\"><i>Dany and the Dragons</i> - Comment</a> (July 9, 2013)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf834-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf834_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf834_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf834_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf834_2-3\">2.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; Beyond the Free Cities&#32;(Sothoryos).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafwyvern_point.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafwyvern_point.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Wyvern Point.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Citadel: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/Heraldry/Houses/7/\">Heraldry - In the Reach</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Prologue\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Prologue\">Prologue</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_54\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 54\">Chapter 54</a>, Davos V.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_14\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 14\">Chapter 14</a>, Tyrion IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfab10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfab10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Jaehaerys and Alysanne - Their Triumphs and Tragedies.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Dictionary.com: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.dictionary.com/browse/wyvern\">WYVERN Definition &amp; Meaning</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;width:100%;color:inherit;;;\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" style=\";\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist\" style=\"display:block;float:left;font-weight:normal;font-size:88%;padding-top:3px;text-align:left;width:6.8em;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/index.php/Template:Animals\" title=\"Template:Animals\"><span title=\"View this template\" style=\";;background:none transparent;border:none;\">v</span></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/index.php?title=Template_talk:Animals&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Template talk:Animals (page does not exist)\"><span title=\"Discuss this template\" style=\";;background:none transparent;border:none;\">d</span></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://awoiaf.westeros.org/index.php?title=Template:Animals&amp;action=edit\"><span title=\"Edit this template\" style=\";;background:none transparent;border:none;\">e</span></a></li></ul></div><div class=\"\" style=\"font-size:110%;\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/Bestiary\" title=\"Bestiary\">Animals of the known world</a></div></th></tr><tr style=\"height:2px;\"><td></td></tr><tr><td scope=\"row\" class=\"navbox-group\" style=\";;\">Birds</td><td style=\"text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px;;;\" class=\"navbox-list navbox-odd\"><div style=\"padding:0em 0.25em\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Bluejay\" title=\"Bluejay\">Bluejay</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Chicken\" title=\"Chicken\">Chicken</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Crane\" title=\"Crane\">Crane</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Crow\" title=\"Crow\">Crow</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Duck\" title=\"Duck\">Duck</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Eagle\" title=\"Eagle\">Eagle</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Falcon\" title=\"Falcon\">Falcon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Goose\" title=\"Goose\">Goose</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Gull\" title=\"G